social_posts.post_text:
I couldn’t have wished for a better end to 2022!   It was a wild 4 months and I feel I need to thank a few people, because it does take a village.
 I want to start with my classmate who have become my friends. It’s going to be hard to explain to people how intense this program was. Thank you all for making this experience so amazing! All the hours studying, stressing, crying but also laughing, have been 100% worth it. It would not have been the same without you all (plus I would not have known what classroom to go to, when assignments were due or what is happening next week) So proud of everyone of you! You all of you have grown so much and will make some kick ass EMT’s and I hope to work with you some day soon!

Secondly my instructors and preceptors (even the ones without Instagram) THANK YOU ALL for pushing me outside my comfort zone, allowing me to make mistakes, giving me constructive criticism and for teaching me to trust the process. I have learned there is no perfect in this job and mistakes will be made and are there to learn from and better ourselves, but I will still keep striving to be the best person I can be and I hope to make you all proud in years to come.

A very special shout out to @mai_tai_22 for checking in on me after every single exam. I appreciate you so much you don’t even know much you’ve done for me! 🖤 #cutie  @brettmcelroy and Hanna for the practice rounds, advice and listening to my worries (and making sure we laugh them away) I know you guys are never in the gram but everyone should know how awesome you both are! 💛  @andreamollermaui for the inspiration and motivation to start this journey in the first place. Thank you for simply being you! I can’t wait for our next adventure 💙

And of course to @captain_jason1 who managed to deal with my stress levels and listened to all my newly gained knowledge (which he already knows) I can wait to roll patients in for you to fix 🤍

It’s official, I’m an EMT now 🚑 🩺 I would say, I hope to see you out there, but honestly I hope
I don’t ❤️ stay safe everyone 😂

(Oh and yes, I’ll finally be available for photo work again 📸)

I don’t do family portraits 🙅🏼‍♀️

I do family moments ✨

It’s still one of my favorite things I’ve ever got the pleasure of shooting, “The Eddie” opening ceremony (this was 2019). I remember the goosebumps I had that day at Waimea bay and how special it felt to just be present there in that moment of time. I just hopped on the plane since “the bay called the day” for the first time since 2016. I’m very excited for everyone who’s honored with an invitation and a little extra excited for the ladies who are part of this event for the first time 🤍! I wish everyone amazing rides, fun and a safe day at the bay! I can’t wait to see the magic and the legend that is Waimea Bay ✨

It’s been full on the past two months. I feel I’ve been shooting non-stop again since I finished school! For which im obviously very grateful 🥲 

During school I didn’t have a single person reach out to me for photo work. I needed that break and time to get through my studies but it obviously worried me a little, I figured well, maybe that was it for the photo career.

However, the moment I finished school and I put my mind towards photography again I got completely slammed. 

It maybe sounds a little woo-woo but I really see this as a reminder how powerful the mind can be and how you can put things out there to have everything ultimately line up for you. ✨

Me and @summermacedo talked about this shoot idea a couple of times and every morning when I drove past this field I thought about how dreamy it would look. I was just so busy and had been getting up every day at 6am to shoot something or another that week… soo I figured what’s another early morning? 🌼✨

Happy we squeezed this session in 💛

#sweetwaterhawaii #mauiphotographer #maui #hawaii #photography #sonyalpha

If you know me, you know that before I was an ocean person I was an absolute horsey girl. I grew up riding, had my own horse and even got put in the hospital for 8 weeks by that hobby. Even though over the years I changed my hobbies and I completely focused on the ocean, I never stopped loving horses. 

This past year horses crept back into my life and I honestly couldn’t be happier! I’ve been shooting some shows here on Maui and I’ve been loving it! Who would’ve guessed that of all the places in the world, I’d find my way back to horses on a tiny island in the middle of the pacific 🤷🏼‍♀️😂

Isn’t it so rad that something like photography can tie into any part of your life.

Now that the 2023 Naish Boxer and Triad are out I finally get to share a couple of shots from my shoot with @naish_kiteboarding !

It was my first time shooting with @naish_kiteboarding and even tho we had less than ideal conditions (is it ever actually ever ideal for any watersports shoot?) we made it happen! I’m stoked to share more of this shoot throughout the next months as more products come out 🙌🏼

Also, I learned a lot of things, like… new words (bantz, skitzing and moff) from the Australians (thanks @kaatiepotter @ewanjaspan @le_tranq) and I also learned from frothmaster Des that being stoked is a lifestyle and that everyone on the team, even tho they said they didn’t, loved Kareoke almost as much as they love Will Ferrel…(@tall_al_oi yea you!)

So many photos I take for clients that never actually make it to my feed.

So here’s a couple of old and new shots I’ve done for @leftonfriday - If you followed me for a while you know I work with them regularly!

I remember when co-owner and founder @lowaks called me and we connected for the first time in 2019. She told me they had just launched their swim wear brand in 2018 and looking to create water related content. Their vision was clear and they knew where they wanted to take the brand 🔥

I called a couple of friends to model and we shot our first frames on Maui soon after!

Fast forward to 2023 and Left on Friday is everywhere! From Sports Illustrated to Vogue, worn by Jessica Alba and styled a complete music video for Kelly Rowland! 

Needless to say I’m so stoked that, even tho they’re grown so much, they still come to me for content! It’s always a pleasure to create with them 🧡

Plus I get to shoot with some of my favorite people 😍

If you don’t know @leftonfriday go check them out. They offer the most amazing swimwear (that really stays on while surfing) and launched a lot of other active/beach wear pieces 😍

⚠️warning⚠️ horsie girl content! 😉

I’ve been wanting to share these photos for a long time. This was a unplanned post family photoshoot, photoshoot. The sun had already set and it was basically getting dark but the girls wanted some photos with the horses. So we ran over to our house, grabbed the unbrushed horses and wandered into the field. 

There’s something so sweet about these little girls with those big horses.

The shots are so imperfect, it’s grainy, it’s dark, the horses are dirty, it’s all unplanned and very random but in my opinion they work. I think it’s because they’re genuine and real.

🤍 sometimes the unplanned photos are the best ones 🤍 (but I’m happy to plan a shoot with you and your horse 😉)

👩🏼👱🏻‍♀️@finnsjumpship
